  "texts": [
    "We have observed that our proposed T-Max-Avg method outperforms max pooling and average pooling, and further improves the accuracy of the Avg-TopK pooling method.",
    "It is more stable than these three methods and demonstrates a higher compatibility rate.",
    "In the proposed T-Max-Avg method, for color images, selecting a pool-size of 4, K value of 6, and T value of 0.7 resulted in the highest score.",
    "For grayscale images, selecting a pool-size of 3, K value of 3, and T value of 0.8 yielded the highest score.",
    "The appropriate learning parameter T may vary depending on the dataset."
  ],
